I just did all my washing.

32:22.775 --> 32:24.902
Because the sun was out.

32:29.365 --> 32:30.908
Hey, Keanu.

32:30.991 --> 32:32.826
This way. Come on.

32:32.910 --> 32:34.119
This way.

32:37.331 --> 32:40.292
You know what lives in the water? Hmm?

32:40.376 --> 32:43.295
-You know what lives in the water? Caiman.
-(growls softly)

32:43.379 --> 32:46.090
And one day, I'm gonna teach you
how to kill a caiman.

32:48.509 --> 32:51.095
I'm trying to teach Keanu that...

32:51.178 --> 32:54.098
he can fucking eat this, you know?

32:54.181 --> 32:57.309
And he's just playing--
like, I don't understand what…

32:57.393 --> 33:00.062
You grab it by the head.

33:03.941 --> 33:06.151
That's what you do-- you grab it.

33:12.241 --> 33:13.867
What is it?

33:18.122 --> 33:19.915
(laughs)

33:21.083 --> 33:22.751
What are you doing?

33:22.835 --> 33:24.086
It's food.

33:25.087 --> 33:27.047
I made such a mess of everything.

33:27.131 --> 33:29.133
You were just a happy kid.

33:30.759 --> 33:32.761
I guess I fixed that, huh?

33:34.930 --> 33:36.932
(insects buzzing)

33:40.185 --> 33:43.313
HARRY:
The sweat bees are attacking our faces.

33:44.398 --> 33:47.317
(sighs) Just absolutely covered.

33:48.819 --> 33:50.237
(sighs)

33:52.114 --> 33:55.409
He's now been playing
with this dead mouse opossum

33:55.492 --> 33:59.163
for like 25 minutes now, and...

33:59.246 --> 34:03.625
the mosquitoes have...
they're driving me a little bit insane.

34:04.710 --> 34:07.755
Eat it. Eat it.

34:07.838 --> 34:10.299
Just eat your rodent.

34:14.303 --> 34:18.556
My body is beaten right now.

34:18.639 --> 34:20.851
(groans)

34:20.934 --> 34:23.645
I'm-I'm sick constantly.

34:23.728 --> 34:25.022
(passes gas)

34:25.105 --> 34:27.983
(laughing):
Oh, that might have been poo.

34:28.065 --> 34:30.985
Oh, no. I think I pooped myself.

34:31.069 --> 34:32.905
(grunts)

34:32.987 --> 34:34.989
(retching)

34:37.576 --> 34:40.120
And I still have months ahead of me.

34:40.204 --> 34:41.914
Keanu, come here.

34:43.123 --> 34:46.335
We need to go back
'cause Harry doesn't feel great.

34:46.418 --> 34:47.795
(sniffles)

34:49.170 --> 34:50.464
Hey, come on.

34:50.547 --> 34:52.632
No, no, don't lay in it.

34:52.716 --> 34:55.010
Follow me. Good boy.

34:55.092 --> 34:56.594
(sniffles)

34:59.598 --> 35:03.560
I've not seen my little brother
in 15 months.

35:05.187 --> 35:08.440
I don't even know how tall he is anymore.

35:08.524 --> 35:11.985
Don't even know what size shoe he is.

35:13.779 --> 35:17.074
Like, I-I can be like,
"Oh, yeah, I'm doing these great things,"

35:17.157 --> 35:21.578
and I'm in the jungle, but...

35:21.662 --> 35:24.957
I'm also missing out on everything,

35:25.040 --> 35:28.585
missing out on all my friends'
and family's lives.

35:35.801 --> 35:37.803
SAMANTHA:
Based on, like, all of my notes

35:37.886 --> 35:41.598
and some habitat data,
I did the road kind of versus trail and...

35:41.682 --> 35:45.060
Larger predators like cats provide
stabilizing functions within ecosystems.

35:45.143 --> 35:47.604
We know they increase biodiversity.

35:47.688 --> 35:50.148
The proceeds from tonight are benefiting
Hoja and the work that we do.

35:50.232 --> 35:51.984
My name is Samantha Zwicker.

35:52.067 --> 35:53.819
I am the founder of Hoja Nueva.

35:53.902 --> 35:55.988
What brought me to the Amazon
was wildlife.

35:56.071 --> 35:59.366
I've always been inspired,
felt connected to wildlife, wild animals.

35:59.449 --> 36:03.620
I think when I made this,
I mean, of course, I loved all animals,

36:03.704 --> 36:07.791
and I had an affinity for cat species,
but at that point, I didn't know

36:07.875 --> 36:09.835
that I wanted to work in conservation.

36:09.918 --> 36:12.379
I loved biology. I thought I was gonna be

36:12.462 --> 36:14.256
-a biologist or a zoologist.
-(meows)

36:14.339 --> 36:16.174
What?

36:17.676 --> 36:19.928
-When I'm around animals, I feel like...
-I love you.

36:20.012 --> 36:21.847
...I can actually be myself and be happy,

36:21.930 --> 36:26.852
whereas being in my family,
I was kind of always on pins and needles

36:26.935 --> 36:28.979
about, like, what was gonna happen
that night.

36:31.481 --> 36:33.901
HEIDI ZWICKER:
Sammy gonna love Harley?

36:34.985 --> 36:36.904
Give Harley a kiss?

36:36.987 --> 36:39.573
-(Samantha barking)
-(Harley moans)

36:39.656 --> 36:42.492
SAMANTHA: I think growing up,
I just had s-such a connection

36:42.576 --> 36:44.703
to each of the animals that I had

36:44.786 --> 36:49.041
that made me trust them more
than I trusted other people in my life.

36:49.124 --> 36:51.335
-Are you recording?
-HEIDI: Uh-huh.

36:52.836 --> 36:55.088
-BRUCE ZWICKER: Sammy?
-Mom, what's this?

36:55.172 --> 36:57.382
BRUCE:
Sammy.

36:57.466 --> 36:59.593
Mees!

36:59.676 --> 37:00.844
What?

37:00.928 --> 37:02.679
Can you say, "I love you, Daddy"?

37:02.763 --> 37:04.389
(quietly):
I love you, Daddy.

37:05.599 --> 37:08.268
-BRUCE: Sammy.
-What?

37:08.352 --> 37:10.270
Say, "I love you, Daddy."

37:10.354 --> 37:11.813
I love you, Daddy.

37:11.897 --> 37:13.774
BRUCE:
You better.

37:16.318 --> 37:18.320
SAMANTHA:
Growing up, going to dinner was

37:18.403 --> 37:21.490
such a horrible experience with my dad,

37:21.573 --> 37:24.576
whether it was, like, him throwing things,

37:24.660 --> 37:27.037
you know, like,
hitting me across the table

37:27.120 --> 37:29.623
or, you know, like, just, like,
horrible experiences,

37:29.706 --> 37:32.501
something so simple
as going to dinner with your family.

37:32.584 --> 37:33.710
YOUNG SAMANTHA:
Come on!

37:33.794 --> 37:37.464
SAMANTHA: Alcoholism makes people say
and do really horrible things.

37:37.547 --> 37:38.882
Hey.

37:40.175 --> 37:43.136
SAMANTHA: We would actually play a game
of, like, counting my dad's shots,

37:43.220 --> 37:47.599
and he always landed around 27 a night.

37:50.394 --> 37:52.229
But... (sighs)

37:52.312 --> 37:56.149
he was also one of
the most kind of playful dads.

37:56.233 --> 37:58.193
Like, a lot of, like, wrestling games.

37:58.276 --> 38:00.153
He always spent a lot of time with us.

38:00.237 --> 38:02.030
(gasps) Look at that top!

38:02.114 --> 38:03.323
Oh, my gosh!

38:03.407 --> 38:06.827
Oh, no, look! No, look at that!

38:06.910 --> 38:08.745
SAMANTHA:
I was scared of him, but at the same time,

38:08.829 --> 38:10.831
I knew it wasn't him, if that makes sense.

38:10.914 --> 38:12.958
Like, from a really young age,
like, I-I could separate

38:13.041 --> 38:16.545
the person that he was when he was drunk
from the person that he really was.

38:17.879 --> 38:19.631
-(roars playfully)
-(laughing)

38:20.716 --> 38:24.344
BRUCE:
There she is, the woman of my dreams.

38:25.429 --> 38:27.305
SAMANTHA:
But my mom and I have this, like...

38:27.389 --> 38:28.807
we have the same, like, tick--

38:28.890 --> 38:31.059
like, this, like, thing
that keeps telling us

38:31.143 --> 38:33.437
to, like, not give up on someone,

38:33.520 --> 38:35.522
because there is that small chance

38:35.605 --> 38:37.733
that what you're doing
is making a difference.

38:37.816 --> 38:39.818
And... (sniffles)

38:39.901 --> 38:41.987
(crying):
And, yeah, I mean, that's the last thing

38:42.070 --> 38:45.407
that my dad ever said to me was:
"Thank you for not giving up on me."

38:45.490 --> 38:47.492
♪ ♪

38:50.120 --> 38:52.122
(birds calling)

38:54.082 --> 38:56.460
(line ringing)

39:08.096 --> 39:10.057
-SAMANTHA (over phone): Hello?
-Hi.

39:10.140 --> 39:12.434
Are you okay? What's going on, Harry?

39:12.517 --> 39:15.312
(crying):
I don't know.

39:19.316 --> 39:22.778
I'm just... I'm just struggling.

39:22.861 --> 39:25.447
(Samantha speaking indistinctly
through static)

39:25.530 --> 39:28.408
You still think you'll be here
Friday or Saturday?

39:31.161 --> 39:32.913
Harry, you cut out.

39:34.831 --> 39:36.666
I'm here. Can you hear me?

39:47.135 --> 39:48.595
(phone beeps)

39:51.098 --> 39:54.309
HARRY:
When I was in Afghanistan,

39:54.392 --> 39:56.561
I had to stop this person

39:56.645 --> 39:58.939
from going to bury his child.

40:00.148 --> 40:04.903
And when I lifted up that blanket

40:04.986 --> 40:08.490
and I saw that little girl's hand
that was just full of blood...

40:10.492 --> 40:12.869
...and then there's my hands, right?

40:12.953 --> 40:16.623
I lifted that blanket up,
and I had my gloves on,

40:16.706 --> 40:20.043
and I had a gun, and I had...

40:20.127 --> 40:22.838
grenades and everything on me.

40:25.048 --> 40:28.093
And then that poor innocent child
was on that bike,

40:28.176 --> 40:31.054
and it's like...

40:31.138 --> 40:33.348
I have no right to be here.

40:40.522 --> 40:44.860
It occurred to me today
that no matter where I am,

40:44.943 --> 40:47.654
who I'm with, what I'm doing,

40:47.737 --> 40:50.282
I'm always gonna have
this fucking problem up here.

40:51.283 --> 40:55.787
(crying): I'm in the most beautiful place
in the world,

40:55.871 --> 40:58.415
and I can't fucking be happy.

41:07.382 --> 41:09.009
(child shouting playfully in distance)

41:12.846 --> 41:14.806
(indistinct chatter)

41:14.890 --> 41:17.976
CHILD:
Samantha! Samantha!

41:19.936 --> 41:22.731
-HARRY: I missed you.
-SAMANTHA: I missed you, too.

41:27.819 --> 41:29.821
(engine starts)

41:36.161 --> 41:37.370
(indistinct chatter)

41:37.454 --> 41:39.414
(chuckles):
Yeah.

41:39.497 --> 41:41.499
(indistinct chatter)

41:47.380 --> 41:49.382
(indistinct chatter)

41:55.472 --> 41:57.807
HARRY:
Mum, wake up.

41:57.891 --> 41:59.768
Mum, I'm gonna scratch my butt
on your face.

41:59.851 --> 42:01.019
Wake up.

42:01.102 --> 42:02.979
Mum, wake up.

42:03.980 --> 42:05.106
(chittering)

42:05.190 --> 42:07.734
Okay. I'm already awake, Max.

42:09.277 --> 42:12.113
♪ ♪

42:15.700 --> 42:17.702
(indistinct chatter)

42:22.999 --> 42:24.376
HARRY:
Kiki?

42:24.459 --> 42:26.127
Mum's here.

42:27.128 --> 42:30.340
SAMANTHA:
Is that my boy? Is that my boy?

42:30.423 --> 42:33.051
(gasps) Are you bigger?

42:33.134 --> 42:34.970
Coming back now,

42:35.053 --> 42:38.640
seeing how large he is and how, like,
confident and how he's, like,

42:38.723 --> 42:41.559
slightly standoffish, you know,
we want him to get to the point

42:41.643 --> 42:44.312
where he doesn't want to see me,

42:44.396 --> 42:47.399
he doesn't want to know me, he doesn't
want to have a connection with me.

42:50.110 --> 42:51.319
(growling)

42:51.403 --> 42:55.115
HARRY:
He's becoming so independent

42:55.198 --> 42:58.535
that it's best that
the-the relationship that he has

42:58.618 --> 43:01.371
is just with a single person, which is me.

43:03.748 --> 43:06.293
We have to make that,
like, line that says,

43:06.376 --> 43:09.671
"Okay, you only can trust
this one person,"

43:09.754 --> 43:12.757
because he needs to realize
that people are dangerous.

43:17.721 --> 43:20.640
SAMANTHA: He had this way already
of communicating with Keanu

43:20.724 --> 43:24.602
and teaching him, and you could just see
that relationship of mother and son.

43:24.686 --> 43:26.938
(Harry growls playfully)

43:34.529 --> 43:36.281
HARRY:
Keanu. (clicks tongue)

43:36.364 --> 43:37.782
Come here.

43:38.867 --> 43:41.119
Good boy. How you doing?

43:41.202 --> 43:43.038
Are you hungry?

43:43.121 --> 43:44.414
(Keanu cries softly)

43:44.497 --> 43:46.374
You're hungry, aren't you?

43:46.458 --> 43:49.210
That's okay. We'll get some food, huh?

43:49.294 --> 43:51.004
Let's go get some rodents. Come on.

43:51.087 --> 43:53.006
Let's go do it.

43:53.089 --> 43:55.216
Don't bite me, all right?

43:57.218 --> 43:58.887
Just pissed on me.

43:58.970 --> 44:00.597
That's great.

44:00.680 --> 44:02.349
Come on, Keanu.

44:07.020 --> 44:08.855
Got to be quicker than that, mate.

44:08.938 --> 44:10.607
Hey!

44:13.693 --> 44:15.737
Keanu, right there.

44:17.197 --> 44:18.656
Keanu.

44:27.415 --> 44:29.876
Keanu almost just caught his first rodent.

44:29.959 --> 44:33.338
He ran after it,
but he didn't manage to get it.

44:33.421 --> 44:35.256
He was so close, though.

44:37.842 --> 44:40.220
(Keanu growling viciously)

44:46.810 --> 44:50.230
He caught his first rodent.
He caught his first rodent!

44:50.313 --> 44:52.774
I'm so happy. I'm so happy.

44:53.858 --> 44:55.568
Mmm, tasty?

44:55.652 --> 44:57.654
(growling softly)

44:59.239 --> 45:01.491
Good boy. I'm proud of you.

45:03.868 --> 45:05.495
I love you.

45:10.542 --> 45:13.503
-Ooh, ooh. Thank you for that kiss.
-(purring)

45:14.671 --> 45:16.381
All right, we'll go back.

45:16.464 --> 45:18.800
Try to find some food on the way.

45:19.884 --> 45:22.345
You looking? I am.

45:27.142 --> 45:29.727
Keanu, that's a wandering spider.

45:31.062 --> 45:32.564
Jesus.

45:33.815 --> 45:35.942
No, that-that's dangerous.

45:36.025 --> 45:37.527
That's a wandering spider.

45:37.610 --> 45:40.280
You see the threat of
that wandering spider there?

45:40.363 --> 45:42.407
That's dangerous, dude.

45:42.490 --> 45:44.742
You okay? Did he get you on the nose?

45:47.579 --> 45:49.080
Keanu.

45:54.919 --> 45:56.296
Hey.

45:56.379 --> 45:58.047
You okay?

45:58.131 --> 45:59.841
Keanu?

46:05.638 --> 46:07.515
Talk to me.

46:07.599 --> 46:09.684
-Are you okay?
-(growls softly)

46:13.521 --> 46:15.398
It's okay. It's okay.

46:15.482 --> 46:17.525
I've got to go get Mummy, okay?

46:17.609 --> 46:19.444
I've got to go get Mummy.

46:21.738 --> 46:23.072
Fuck's sake.

46:24.157 --> 46:25.700
I'll be back.

46:26.826 --> 46:28.661
Give me two seconds, okay?

46:29.954 --> 46:31.748
I'll be back.

46:34.918 --> 46:36.085
(sighs)

46:36.169 --> 46:37.837
Fuck me.

46:37.921 --> 46:40.006
♪ ♪

46:48.556 --> 46:52.852
SAMANTHA: Keanu was bit
by a Brazilian wandering spider,

46:52.936 --> 46:56.272
and he had partial... partial paralysis

46:56.356 --> 46:59.484
and, um, slowed breathing,

46:59.567 --> 47:03.571
and, um, his heart rate started going up
really, really fast.

47:03.655 --> 47:07.700
Um, and after about
an hour and a half now,

47:07.784 --> 47:09.911
he's starting to get a little bit better.

47:09.994 --> 47:12.664
Um, definitely the biggest scare
that we've had

47:12.747 --> 47:15.250
since starting this project.

47:15.333 --> 47:17.085
HARRY:
You doing better, eh?

47:18.294 --> 47:21.422
Hey. I know, it still hurts.

47:23.550 --> 47:26.886
SAMANTHA: I feel like he's putting so much
on this project with Keanu

47:26.970 --> 47:29.847
that it's almost like his redemption.

47:34.686 --> 47:37.397
And part of me is like...
of course, I-I mean,

47:37.480 --> 47:39.482
I want Keanu to be successful
for so many reasons,

47:39.566 --> 47:42.277
but one of the main reasons
I want him to be successful is because

47:42.360 --> 47:44.487
I want Harry to finally
be able to move on.

47:52.287 --> 47:54.497
(distant gunshot)

47:54.581 --> 47:56.457
(Harry sighs)

47:57.542 --> 48:00.920
Last night, I heard a gunshot.
Tonight, I've heard a gunshot.

48:04.048 --> 48:05.925
(sighs) I need to find out who it is.

48:06.009 --> 48:07.885
I need to find out where they're hunting.

48:07.969 --> 48:10.680
I need to find out what they're hunting.

48:12.682 --> 48:15.310
I hate gunshots now.

48:15.393 --> 48:16.477
(groans)

48:20.023 --> 48:22.025
A shotgun, for sure.

48:27.488 --> 48:30.533
We still know that people hunt
with illegal shotgun traps.

48:30.617 --> 48:32.827
There are still all of these things that,

48:32.910 --> 48:36.581
after what happened to Khan,
deeply scare us even more now.

48:36.664 --> 48:40.043
And it's really difficult working
in an unprotected area.

48:43.713 --> 48:46.674
This region is known for deforestation
from logging practices,

48:46.758 --> 48:50.053
about 89% which are illegal.

48:52.764 --> 48:55.767
-Hear the chain saw clearer now?
-(chain saw buzzing in distance)

48:55.850 --> 48:58.603
That's extremely close to our border.

48:58.686 --> 49:00.480
(chain saw continues)

49:00.563 --> 49:02.565
(chain saw stops)

49:05.777 --> 49:09.197
I heard the chain saw,
and I come up here-- chain saw stops.

49:10.406 --> 49:12.825
This is what you'll find all around here.

49:16.245 --> 49:18.331
Just full of shotgun shells.

49:18.414 --> 49:21.125
(chain saw buzzing)

49:24.754 --> 49:26.756
(Samantha speaking Spanish)

49:28.091 --> 49:30.593
SAMANTHA: We came across
a group of guys cutting the tree.

49:30.677 --> 49:34.764
You know, told them that they were
on our land and they needed to leave.

49:34.847 --> 49:36.391
But it was too late, obviously.

49:36.474 --> 49:41.562
This is a almost 1,000-year-old lupuna
that was already cut.

49:43.898 --> 49:46.609
The quickest way for someone
to make money here

49:46.693 --> 49:49.696
is usually mining or-or logging.

49:49.779 --> 49:53.116
And so you can't really point fingers
at the people who are actively cutting,

49:53.199 --> 49:55.576
because they aren't usually
the ones that are involved

49:55.660 --> 49:57.787
in all these international dealings.

49:59.288 --> 50:02.500
There are so many challenges
that you face in conservation,

50:02.583 --> 50:04.627
and this is one of them.

50:04.711 --> 50:06.713
♪ ♪

50:14.220 --> 50:17.014
I can still hear that chain saw
in the west.

50:17.098 --> 50:19.225
(chain saw buzzing)

50:20.393 --> 50:23.146
Fuck, I can hear
that chain saw getting louder.

50:23.229 --> 50:25.982
I'm having to put him back,

50:26.065 --> 50:30.361
even though he does not want it,
because this is more important.

50:30.445 --> 50:32.655
(chain saw buzzing loudly)

50:32.739 --> 50:35.032
I'll be back. We'll go on a walk tonight.

50:35.116 --> 50:36.659
(grunts softly)

50:36.743 --> 50:38.745
(chain saw continues buzzing)

50:45.418 --> 50:46.753
I don't know.

50:52.008 --> 50:55.219
I have no idea where
this chain saw's coming from.

50:58.556 --> 51:01.225
I feel so...

51:01.309 --> 51:03.311
I can't even explain it.

51:03.394 --> 51:04.896
(sniffles)

51:07.398 --> 51:11.152
I just feel like I'm not in control
of my own self right now.

51:11.235 --> 51:15.156
I can't control my anger
or my hate or my...

51:15.239 --> 51:17.825
I can't control anything right now.

51:17.909 --> 51:18.993
(sniffles)

51:23.956 --> 51:26.459
I kind of just want to cut myself.

51:30.880 --> 51:32.882
(birds calling)

51:52.944 --> 51:54.946
♪ ♪

51:58.699 --> 52:03.579
SAMANTHA:
He genuinely believes that cutting himself

52:03.663 --> 52:07.124
and, like, seeing blood, feeling the pain

52:07.208 --> 52:09.544
and, like, the tingling, as he calls it,

52:09.627 --> 52:14.173
he genuinely feels that that helps him
to get over a panic attack.

52:15.258 --> 52:17.802
Um, or to get over his rage.

52:21.013 --> 52:22.723
And for me,

52:22.807 --> 52:24.934
I-I have a worry about, like,

52:25.017 --> 52:27.603
how much worse it could've gotten
if he didn't calm down.

52:31.023 --> 52:35.403
HARRY: After Afghanistan,
I was in such a bad place,

52:35.486 --> 52:37.822
I didn't really think about
what I was doing,

52:37.905 --> 52:40.658
and I tried to kill myself in my bedroom.

52:41.909 --> 52:45.246
Yeah, and-and I woke up,

52:45.329 --> 52:48.124
and I just felt ridiculous.

52:51.085 --> 52:54.672
I didn't want my little brother
to find his older brother dead.

52:55.673 --> 52:57.091
WOMAN:
Say hello, Jayden.

52:57.174 --> 52:59.760
-YOUNG HARRY: Hello, Jayden.
-WOMAN: Hello!

52:59.844 --> 53:03.055
HARRY: When I was 13,
my brother came into the picture.

53:03.139 --> 53:06.434
YOUNG HARRY:
Big, strong tiger.

53:06.517 --> 53:08.686
HARRY:
And he really changed my life.

53:08.769 --> 53:12.398
I really, you know,
wanted him to look up to me,

53:12.481 --> 53:14.692
and I really wanted to take care of him.

53:15.693 --> 53:18.154
It's Harry Potter
and the Half-Blood Prince!

53:18.237 --> 53:19.864
-(laughter)
-Look.

53:19.947 --> 53:22.825
-Wow!
-HARRY: Are you happy?

53:22.909 --> 53:26.037
Yeah? Good.

53:26.120 --> 53:31.667
I did not want my little brother to...
to see his brother in pain anymore.

53:38.466 --> 53:41.344
And that's why I booked
a flight to the jungle.

53:44.180 --> 53:49.310
I was just pissed off and wanted to...
just wanted to, like, feel some pain.

53:49.393 --> 53:51.687
I hardly bled. I didn't want to bleed.

53:51.771 --> 53:53.814
I didn't want to cut myself deeply.

53:53.898 --> 53:56.859
You're clearly just like...

53:56.943 --> 53:59.070
disappointed in me.

53:59.153 --> 54:01.364
I'm not disappointed, Harry.

54:02.865 --> 54:04.659
You just worry me.

54:07.703 --> 54:09.705
(lively chatter)

54:16.963 --> 54:20.508
SAMANTHA: Lidia!
I'm going to leave this bottle of wine.

54:20.591 --> 54:22.093
It's for Harry's parents.

54:22.176 --> 54:24.387
They're coming for the first time
tomorrow.

54:24.470 --> 54:26.764
They are going to come with his brother.

54:26.847 --> 54:28.182
He's thirteen.

54:28.265 --> 54:30.434
-Are they coming tomorrow?
-They're coming tomorrow.

54:31.477 --> 54:33.479
Okay, perfect. Thank you.

54:33.562 --> 54:35.564
See you tomorrow.

54:38.442 --> 54:40.444
(birds whistling)

54:42.154 --> 54:43.906
HARRY:
For a year and a half,

54:43.990 --> 54:47.743
I've only heard their voices
on the satellite phone.

54:49.578 --> 54:51.747
And that's like once a month.

54:54.250 --> 54:57.003
SAMANTHA: What do you think
it's gonna be like when you see them?

54:57.086 --> 54:59.088
(chuckles)

55:02.675 --> 55:05.428
(laughter, indistinct chatter)

55:05.511 --> 55:07.471
♪ ♪

55:07.555 --> 55:09.515
It's gonna be really nice.

55:13.686 --> 55:15.104
MARK TURNER:
This is probably the furthest we've ever

55:15.187 --> 55:17.857
-been away from civilization.
-COLETTE TURNER (chuckles): Definitely.

55:17.940 --> 55:19.025
(laughter)

55:19.108 --> 55:21.068
HARRY: Bet it's gonna be great
when my little brother

55:21.152 --> 55:23.654
can see an anaconda.

55:23.738 --> 55:27.658
He loves insects as well, so I caught
a massive tarantula the other day,

55:27.742 --> 55:31.829
and I... all I could think about
was how, like...

55:31.912 --> 55:33.914
how Jayden would just love it.

55:33.998 --> 55:35.583
(excited chatter, gasping)

55:35.666 --> 55:37.168
JAYDEN:
Harry!

55:37.251 --> 55:39.378
-MARK: Mum wants first hug.
-JAYDEN: Mum gets first hug.

55:39.462 --> 55:41.422
(laughter)

55:41.505 --> 55:43.507
JAYDEN:
I call seconds!

55:47.928 --> 55:49.638
-How you doing?
-I'm good. How are you?

55:49.722 --> 55:52.183
-Oh, I'm all right.
-(sighs)

55:55.603 --> 55:58.522
MARK:
Jesus, Harry, I'm so impressed.

55:58.606 --> 56:00.191
(laughing)

56:00.274 --> 56:02.485
12 years in the Navy,
I've never seen driving like his.

56:08.574 --> 56:10.910
-HARRY: Here.
-MARK: Okay.

56:10.993 --> 56:12.661
So, we've got the master bedroom?

56:12.745 --> 56:14.121
-SAMANTHA: Yes, you do.
-Is that right?

56:14.205 --> 56:15.748
At least we've got walls.

56:15.831 --> 56:17.833
A little bit of privacy.

56:17.917 --> 56:19.752
SAMANTHA: Right here,
if you're going to the bathroom

56:19.835 --> 56:21.462
and you don't want anyone else to join,

56:21.545 --> 56:23.172
-you can just put this little...
-MARK: Oh!

56:23.255 --> 56:24.799
-...string up right here.
-COLETTE: Okay.

56:26.217 --> 56:28.010
MARK:
Oh, fucking hell.

56:28.094 --> 56:30.554
HARRY:
Oh, Jay, I made you a fishing rod.

56:30.638 --> 56:32.765
-Thank you.
-And a machete.

56:32.848 --> 56:34.850
Wait, what do you mean, made me a machete?

56:34.934 --> 56:37.812
Well, it was broken,
so I made it into a mini machete.

56:39.313 --> 56:41.398
-That's huge!
-What do you mean, "that's huge"?

56:41.482 --> 56:43.400
It was this long, and it was snapped off,

56:43.484 --> 56:46.278
so then I decided to chip it off
with a hammer

56:46.362 --> 56:48.489
and then make a little machete for you.

56:48.572 --> 56:49.782
Thank you.

56:49.865 --> 56:51.075
(indistinct chatter)

56:51.158 --> 56:52.618
HARRY:
All right, okay.

56:52.701 --> 56:55.412
I need to walk Keanu,
and you're probably gonna go to bed.

56:55.496 --> 56:58.541
Um, don't know when I'll come back,
so good night.

57:05.297 --> 57:07.883
I've come to give you some food
so that tomorrow

57:07.967 --> 57:10.553
we can go out and get some videos

57:10.636 --> 57:13.848
so I can show my family.

57:13.931 --> 57:15.599
My family are here.

57:15.683 --> 57:17.518
Your grandparents are here!

57:20.771 --> 57:22.773
(footsteps splashing)

57:32.867 --> 57:35.161
There's a big caiman here, dude.

57:39.290 --> 57:40.958
Could be dangerous.

57:41.041 --> 57:44.128
Uh-uh-uh-uh-uh. Uh-uh-uh-uh-uh.

57:44.211 --> 57:45.671
No. No.

57:45.754 --> 57:48.757
Uh-uh. No.

57:48.841 --> 57:51.385
Don't do it. Do not do it.

57:53.554 --> 57:56.849
(exclaims) Fucking hell.

57:57.933 --> 57:59.560
(exhales heavily)

57:59.643 --> 58:01.937
Holy shit, I'm shaking.

58:06.817 --> 58:08.944
You doing okay, man?

58:09.028 --> 58:10.821
You okay?

58:10.905 --> 58:12.698
(laughs)

58:13.949 --> 58:17.536
(laughing):
You scared the shit out of me.

58:17.620 --> 58:21.415
You scared the shit right out of me.

58:21.498 --> 58:23.584
(sighs heavily)

58:24.585 --> 58:26.587
(birds calling)

58:33.594 --> 58:36.055
HARRY: So, what do your friends think
about you coming out here?

58:36.138 --> 58:38.682
(laughs)
They've started calling me Mowgli.

58:38.766 --> 58:40.559
-Mowgli?
-(laughs)

58:40.643 --> 58:42.853
-You haven't got the hair for it.
-I know.

58:42.937 --> 58:44.939
(both laugh)

58:46.732 --> 58:48.442
They jealous?

58:48.525 --> 58:49.735
No, not really.

58:49.818 --> 58:52.112
They're like,
"Why would you want to go to a place

58:52.196 --> 58:54.573
"with no, um, Internet, no nothing?

58:54.657 --> 58:56.617
I'd rather just go to Florida." (laughs)

58:56.700 --> 58:59.245
-HARRY: That bloody generation, huh?
-JAYDEN: Yeah.

59:00.996 --> 59:02.790
Did you bring your iPhone?

59:02.873 --> 59:04.667
-No.
-You left it.

59:04.750 --> 59:07.628
-I brought an iPod
so I could listen to music. -Mm.

59:09.505 --> 59:11.840
You hear what that... you hear that...
(makes whooshing sound)

59:11.924 --> 59:14.343
-That was a hummingbird.
-(chuckles)

59:14.426 --> 59:15.844
They, like, fly through the house.

59:15.928 --> 59:18.681
(makes whooshing sound, mutters)

59:18.764 --> 59:20.849
-What's that?
-Termite nest, yeah.

59:23.519 --> 59:25.396
Tree termites. (laughs)

59:25.479 --> 59:27.231
There's termites everywhere.

59:27.314 --> 59:29.191
We had to put diesel in this platform

59:29.275 --> 59:31.443
because the termites come up
and try to eat everything.

59:32.528 --> 59:33.988
What are these?

59:34.071 --> 59:35.906
-Scars?
-Yeah.

59:38.033 --> 59:41.370
These ones up here, all these cuts
from up here are from Keanu.

59:41.453 --> 59:46.125
This, like, blotch here and, like, here
is where I got burnt by the acid.

59:46.208 --> 59:48.210
Oh, acid? Did that heal all right, did it?

59:48.294 --> 59:49.461
Yeah, it healed all right.

59:49.545 --> 59:53.132
I had one bit that was in my hand,
which was... got infected, but...

59:53.215 --> 59:55.342
And how'd you get those ones, the stripes?

59:55.426 --> 59:58.387
Um, some were from Keanu
and some were from myself.

1:00:00.764 --> 1:00:02.349
-Hmm.
-Painful?

1:00:02.433 --> 1:00:03.600
Yeah.

1:00:05.602 --> 1:00:09.398
Um, so I-I didn't know
whether you guys wanted to go fishing.

1:00:11.567 --> 1:00:13.277
-Do you want to go fishing, Jay?
-Yeah.

1:00:13.360 --> 1:00:14.945
Okay. Cool.

1:00:16.613 --> 1:00:18.615
(indistinct chatter)

1:00:20.117 --> 1:00:22.828
-(chuckles)
-MARK: Oh, my God! (laughs)

1:00:22.911 --> 1:00:24.747
HARRY:
Go. Go, go, go.

1:00:26.457 --> 1:00:28.792
Ah, we're gonna crash! (laughing)

1:00:30.252 --> 1:00:31.462
(lively chatter)

1:00:31.545 --> 1:00:33.213
HARRY:
See? Perfect.

1:00:33.297 --> 1:00:36.008
♪ ♪

1:00:41.305 --> 1:00:43.682
HARRY:
That's definitely Jayden's dinner.

1:00:44.767 --> 1:00:46.643
So, hold the fin like that.

1:00:46.727 --> 1:00:49.438
(indistinct chatter)

1:00:49.521 --> 1:00:52.358
-You think you're gonna be all right?
-Oh. Yeah.

1:00:52.441 --> 1:00:54.985
-(splash)
-(laughing)

1:00:57.029 --> 1:00:59.490
-What?
-I'm sinking!

1:01:02.868 --> 1:01:05.329
Do it. Dive in!

1:01:09.166 --> 1:01:10.584
No!

1:01:10.667 --> 1:01:12.669
(laughter)

1:01:15.756 --> 1:01:17.591
HARRY:
All right.

1:01:18.801 --> 1:01:21.220
-COLETTE: My God.
-JAYDEN: Oh, my God.

1:01:21.303 --> 1:01:23.305
Wow.

1:01:24.556 --> 1:01:26.266
MARK:
Oh, my God, I tell you what,

1:01:26.350 --> 1:01:28.894
Disneyland's never gonna
be the same again, is it?

1:01:28.977 --> 1:01:31.230
♪ ♪

1:01:34.525 --> 1:01:35.859
JAYDEN:
Whoo!

1:01:35.943 --> 1:01:38.487
HARRY:
Amazing bugs in this part of the world.

1:01:38.570 --> 1:01:41.281
Wait, that's a praying mantis. (gasps)

1:01:43.242 --> 1:01:46.286
I haven't even seen
a praying mantis at a pet shop.

1:01:46.370 --> 1:01:47.496
HARRY:
Really?

1:01:47.579 --> 1:01:49.456
(gasps) Oh, my God.

1:01:51.208 --> 1:01:52.626
(laughs)

1:01:56.171 --> 1:01:58.382
-Is it a vicious one?
-HARRY: No.

1:01:58.465 --> 1:02:00.467
It's called a bluntheaded tree snake.

1:02:01.885 --> 1:02:05.097
JAYDEN: Okay, this is officially
the coolest day of my life.

1:02:11.603 --> 1:02:14.314
♪ ♪

1:02:24.533 --> 1:02:26.243
Oh, look at that.

1:02:30.038 --> 1:02:31.623
-JAYDEN: Hey.
-SAMANTHA: How'd it go?

1:02:31.707 --> 1:02:33.959
-JAYDEN: We saw nothing.
-HARRY: Zero.

1:02:34.042 --> 1:02:35.961
JAYDEN:
The only things we saw

1:02:36.044 --> 1:02:38.338
were, um, two different types of snake,

1:02:38.422 --> 1:02:40.757
-four different types of tarantulas...
-MARK: What? What?

1:02:40.841 --> 1:02:44.428
...a frog, a whip scorpion. (laughs)

1:02:44.511 --> 1:02:46.346
MARK:
Did you have the best time ever?

1:02:46.430 --> 1:02:47.681
(indistinct chatter, laughter)

1:02:47.764 --> 1:02:49.099
Oh, here. Look at this, right?

1:02:49.183 --> 1:02:50.767
-What is it?
-It's a tarantula.

1:02:52.644 --> 1:02:56.482
HARRY (laughing): He... he grabbed it
and went like this and threw it on me.

1:02:56.565 --> 1:02:59.026
(laughter)

1:03:00.110 --> 1:03:02.154
HARRY: I'm sad that you're
going to be leaving tomorrow.

1:03:02.237 --> 1:03:03.989
JAYDEN:
I'm sad I'm gonna be leaving.

1:03:05.073 --> 1:03:06.575
The best holiday of my life.

1:03:06.658 --> 1:03:09.119
(Jayden squealing, shouting indistinctly)

1:03:10.954 --> 1:03:12.039
Go on.

1:03:12.122 --> 1:03:14.291
-(whoops, laughs)
-(others laughing)

1:03:16.418 --> 1:03:18.253
♪ ♪

1:03:21.381 --> 1:03:22.966
(laughs)

1:03:25.469 --> 1:03:27.554
You guys are gonna be heading soon, so...

1:03:27.638 --> 1:03:29.389
Lovely seeing you again, mate.

1:03:29.473 --> 1:03:30.766
JAYDEN:
Good to see you.

1:03:32.559 --> 1:03:34.353
-I love you, man.
-I love you.

1:03:34.436 --> 1:03:36.063
-Take it easy.
-Uh-huh.

1:03:36.146 --> 1:03:38.190
All right. I love you.

1:03:38.273 --> 1:03:39.775
Mwah.

1:03:39.858 --> 1:03:41.902
I'm really proud of you.

1:03:41.985 --> 1:03:43.904
-I'm glad you enjoyed it.
-I've really enjoyed it.

1:03:43.987 --> 1:03:45.405
-HARRY: Yeah.
-COLETTE: It's been brilliant.

1:03:45.489 --> 1:03:47.449
I've been really impressed
with what you've achieved.

1:03:47.533 --> 1:03:49.243
It's an amazing story.

1:03:49.326 --> 1:03:51.161
Oh. Thanks, Jay.

1:03:51.245 --> 1:03:53.247
-I'll see you soon, okay? Yeah.
-See you soon. Yeah.

1:03:54.831 --> 1:03:57.834
Um, can I ask one thing, though?

1:03:57.918 --> 1:04:00.212
When I come back,
can you make chicken pie for me?

1:04:00.295 --> 1:04:02.172
-'Cause that's all I crave.
-Of course I can.

1:04:02.256 --> 1:04:03.799
-(laughing): That's all I crave.
-Of course.

1:04:03.882 --> 1:04:05.884
The funny thing is
I cut these onions and garlics,

1:04:05.968 --> 1:04:07.678
and my fingers smell
like your chicken pie.

1:04:07.761 --> 1:04:10.430
And I walk around the jungle
with my light next to my face

1:04:10.514 --> 1:04:13.225
just thinking about your chicken pie
all the time.

1:04:16.436 --> 1:04:18.105
Don't get upset.

1:04:19.356 --> 1:04:20.899
I'll see you soon, all right?

1:04:23.443 --> 1:04:25.696
-I love you lots.
-Love you, too.

1:04:27.030 --> 1:04:28.740
You take care of you.

1:04:28.824 --> 1:04:30.367
Of course.

1:04:32.536 --> 1:04:34.663
SAMANTHA:
No crying. You make me cry.

1:04:34.746 --> 1:04:37.416
-(Samantha laughing)
-I wasn't...

1:04:37.499 --> 1:04:39.668
I wasn't going to.

1:04:41.253 --> 1:04:43.380
You guys coming made him so happy.

1:04:44.715 --> 1:04:46.341
I got it from here. Don't worry.

1:04:46.425 --> 1:04:48.719
HARRY: You enjoy your, uh,
next week ahead of you.

1:04:48.802 --> 1:04:50.804
Adios.

1:04:50.887 --> 1:04:52.889
Bye, guys.

1:04:52.973 --> 1:04:54.308
SAMANTHA:
Travel safe, yeah?

1:04:55.392 --> 1:04:57.603
(vehicle departing)

1:04:57.686 --> 1:04:59.521
SAMANTHA (laughing):
Aw, look at Jayden. He's still waving.

1:04:59.605 --> 1:05:01.356
HARRY:
Aw, he's still waving.

1:05:01.440 --> 1:05:03.400
(birds calling)

1:05:03.483 --> 1:05:05.485
♪ ♪

1:05:07.779 --> 1:05:09.531
HARRY (laughing):
Hey.

1:05:12.242 --> 1:05:14.244
-Come on.
-(growling softly)

1:05:21.376 --> 1:05:23.503
(growling softly)

1:05:24.588 --> 1:05:27.507
HARRY: Around 14 months
is when he starts leaving his mother.

1:05:27.591 --> 1:05:28.925
(growls, hisses)

1:05:30.969 --> 1:05:32.596
(snarls)

1:05:32.679 --> 1:05:35.724
I see the next few months

1:05:35.807 --> 1:05:38.977
being a big separation period.

1:05:40.354 --> 1:05:42.356
(crying):
I'm gonna miss you, man.

1:05:43.565 --> 1:05:46.276
I'm gonna miss you so much.

1:05:51.615 --> 1:05:53.742
He's aggressive. He's ferocious.

1:05:53.825 --> 1:05:56.787
He's feisty and mean.

1:05:59.206 --> 1:06:00.499
Watch out.

1:06:00.582 --> 1:06:02.626
Watch out. It's gonna bite ya.

1:06:02.709 --> 1:06:04.544
Watch out.

1:06:04.628 --> 1:06:09.091
He's eating, hunting, you know,
doing what an ocelot should do.

1:06:09.174 --> 1:06:11.385
(growling)

1:06:12.469 --> 1:06:14.471
(dog barking in distance)

1:06:16.139 --> 1:06:17.557
Cristian, Niery.

1:06:17.641 --> 1:06:19.559
Tomorrow I'm going to the United States.

1:06:19.643 --> 1:06:22.270
It's possible that I'll be back
in September.

1:06:22.354 --> 1:06:24.773
If there's something urgent
just let me know.

1:06:26.316 --> 1:06:28.068
Okay, bye!

1:06:28.151 --> 1:06:29.695
See you later.

1:06:29.778 --> 1:06:31.071
Bye, guys. (blows kiss)

1:06:31.154 --> 1:06:32.572
Good luck.

1:06:33.657 --> 1:06:35.659
-(insects trilling)
-(birds calling)

1:06:38.662 --> 1:06:40.664
HARRY:
For him to become truly wild,

1:06:40.747 --> 1:06:42.749
I need to let him be alone.

1:06:44.167 --> 1:06:46.503
I need to give him some freedom.

1:06:51.174 --> 1:06:53.009
There's an egg for you there.

1:06:55.554 --> 1:06:57.472
But that's it.

1:06:57.556 --> 1:06:59.558
No more.

1:06:59.641 --> 1:07:01.143
Now, don't follow me.

1:07:01.226 --> 1:07:03.645
Eat your egg. Don't follow me.

1:07:13.613 --> 1:07:16.074
-(insects trilling)
-(fire crackling)

1:07:16.158 --> 1:07:19.870
It's the first night he's ever spent
out of his enclosure, full night.

1:07:25.751 --> 1:07:29.129
I feel a little bit lonely

1:07:29.212 --> 1:07:31.965
knowing that he's gone, for now.

1:07:33.800 --> 1:07:39.055
Just the fact that you've had something
in your life for so many months,

1:07:39.139 --> 1:07:42.184
and then... it's, you know, relied on you,

1:07:42.267 --> 1:07:45.437
and now he's old enough to go.

1:07:50.108 --> 1:07:53.570
What if this is the last time
I ever see him?

1:07:53.653 --> 1:07:56.364
'Cause there aren't really
any guidelines for this.

1:07:56.448 --> 1:07:59.201
We're just having to make it up.

1:08:00.994 --> 1:08:04.539
It's just tough knowing that
I'm not his safety net anymore.

1:08:07.125 --> 1:08:09.127
♪ ♪

1:08:28.313 --> 1:08:30.314
♪ ♪

1:08:50.585 --> 1:08:52.587
(birds chirping)

1:09:07.269 --> 1:09:09.104
(sighs)

1:09:21.032 --> 1:09:23.451
He's not here. He's not been back.

1:09:26.955 --> 1:09:28.915
(computer chimes)

1:09:31.667 --> 1:09:35.337
That's the male we have a problem with,

1:09:35.421 --> 1:09:37.591
and he was here last night.

1:09:39.384 --> 1:09:40.926
Me.

1:09:49.895 --> 1:09:52.104
(indistinct chatter)

1:09:53.773 --> 1:09:55.483
Fuck.

1:10:00.614 --> 1:10:02.782
Uh, the next camera's just up here.

1:10:08.580 --> 1:10:10.290
Oh!

1:10:11.291 --> 1:10:13.501
Keanu's here at 7:21 a.m.

1:10:14.628 --> 1:10:16.421
Kiki?

1:10:18.214 --> 1:10:19.633
7:21.

1:10:20.717 --> 1:10:22.636
I know it's him.

1:10:25.680 --> 1:10:27.974
I'm gonna walk the stream trail.

1:10:32.646 --> 1:10:34.814
Hey, Keanu.

1:10:34.898 --> 1:10:38.276
(chuckling):
Hello, mate. Hello, mate.

1:10:39.527 --> 1:10:41.363
(laughs)

1:10:41.446 --> 1:10:43.573
(Keanu purring)

1:10:43.657 --> 1:10:45.825
You've done so good.

1:10:45.909 --> 1:10:47.911
(laughing)

1:10:58.505 --> 1:11:00.423
Oh, my God.

1:11:00.507 --> 1:11:04.135
(laughing):
I fucking love you so much.

1:11:05.303 --> 1:11:07.389
(Keanu purring)

1:11:08.932 --> 1:11:10.934
(Harry sighs)

1:11:11.017 --> 1:11:12.644
Tell me I'm being an idiot.

1:11:12.727 --> 1:11:14.980
(laughing):
Tell me I'm being an idiot.

1:11:24.614 --> 1:11:26.449
Oh, dear me.

1:11:26.533 --> 1:11:29.244
Uh-uh, not my laptop, not my laptop.
(laughs)

1:11:31.246 --> 1:11:32.872
(sniffling)

1:11:32.956 --> 1:11:34.958
Not my laptop.

1:11:36.334 --> 1:11:38.169
(sighs)

1:11:39.379 --> 1:11:41.881
You spent the whole night out, mate.

1:11:44.676 --> 1:11:46.428
(sighs)

1:11:48.096 --> 1:11:50.306
I'm so proud of you, man.

1:11:51.808 --> 1:11:53.977
We got to do it again tonight.

1:11:55.020 --> 1:11:57.022
(laughing)

1:12:03.153 --> 1:12:05.071
(insects chirping)

1:12:13.788 --> 1:12:15.665
Cristian.

1:12:15.749 --> 1:12:17.333
SAMANTHA:
You cleaned.

1:12:19.669 --> 1:12:21.212
HARRY:
That was a long trip, eh?

1:12:21.296 --> 1:12:22.797
-(Samantha yawns)
-HARRY: How you doing?

1:12:22.881 --> 1:12:25.383
SAMANTHA:
Did you paint that thing on your lip?

1:12:25.467 --> 1:12:27.385
-(laughs)
-It's my mustache.

1:12:27.469 --> 1:12:28.845
I'm growing a mustache.

1:12:28.928 --> 1:12:31.139
This is fucking like 22 days in the...
in the making.

1:12:31.222 --> 1:12:32.682
-Get out of here.
-What?

1:12:32.766 --> 1:12:35.226
You painted that.
There's no way you can actually grow that.

1:12:35.310 --> 1:12:36.853
-Yeah.
-Oh, my God.

1:12:36.936 --> 1:12:38.563
I'm... This is my Movember.

1:12:38.646 --> 1:12:41.316
-I'm starting it in... in August.
-Okay. Okay, cool.

1:12:41.399 --> 1:12:44.778
This is the first... the video of Keanu
on the camera trap for that...

1:12:44.861 --> 1:12:46.279
he was out the whole night.

1:12:46.362 --> 1:12:48.573
-Okay.
-So he was there at 7:21,

1:12:48.656 --> 1:12:52.035
and then I come
and I check the thing at 8:17.

1:12:52.118 --> 1:12:55.163
And then when I walk down that trail,
that's when I find him.

1:12:55.246 --> 1:12:57.165
-Gosh.
-Yeah.

1:12:57.248 --> 1:12:58.541
I like it. It's okay.

1:12:58.625 --> 1:12:59.793
-No, you don't.
-I like it!

1:12:59.876 --> 1:13:01.377
SAMANTHA:
Once he stopped keeping Keanu

1:13:01.461 --> 1:13:03.671
in the enclosure during the day,
like, that was huge.

1:13:03.755 --> 1:13:06.174
I mean, for Keanu to be able
to go in and out

1:13:06.257 --> 1:13:08.885
and, like, to be just out
in the jungle is... it seems crazy.

1:13:08.968 --> 1:13:11.679
Like, we never got to that point
with Khan. He was almost there.

1:13:11.763 --> 1:13:15.308
He was within, like, a week of being that,
but we weren't there.

1:13:16.976 --> 1:13:20.647
Right, I'll see you
in, um, 15, 20 minutes.

1:13:25.860 --> 1:13:28.029
(insects buzzing)

1:13:29.114 --> 1:13:30.865
You-you heard him, right?

1:13:31.866 --> 1:13:33.076
I definitely heard him.

1:13:33.159 --> 1:13:34.702
He's just looking for Harry, I bet.

1:13:36.412 --> 1:13:38.039
Harry?

1:13:40.166 --> 1:13:42.293
Kiki, go on.

1:13:42.377 --> 1:13:45.046
You can't be here. You know that.

1:13:45.130 --> 1:13:47.298
You shouldn't be eating lemongrass.

1:13:51.010 --> 1:13:53.555
It's just weird, him being,
like, out of his enclosure.

1:13:53.638 --> 1:13:57.350
It's like... now he knows,
like, where Harry lives.

1:13:57.433 --> 1:14:00.812
(laughing):
It's... so crazy.

1:14:02.856 --> 1:14:04.774
Harry?

1:14:04.858 --> 1:14:06.860
(retching)

1:14:08.486 --> 1:14:11.114
HARRY:
Last night was bad.

1:14:11.197 --> 1:14:14.868
Keanu just kept coming back
to the platform constantly.

1:14:14.951 --> 1:14:16.244
(sighs)

1:14:16.327 --> 1:14:18.163
Probably why he keeps coming back
to the platform--

1:14:18.246 --> 1:14:20.456
to tell me that he's hungry.

1:14:22.083 --> 1:14:25.295
I can't... can't be that person
for him anymore, though.

1:14:25.378 --> 1:14:27.380
(sniffing)

1:14:28.673 --> 1:14:31.843
He needs to know that I'm not that person.

1:14:31.926 --> 1:14:34.095
And I don't know how to tell him that.

1:14:34.179 --> 1:14:37.891
I don't know how to tell him to...
to move on. (sniffles)

1:14:37.974 --> 1:14:39.267
(Keanu growling)

1:14:39.350 --> 1:14:40.894
HARRY:
I'll leave you.

1:14:42.353 --> 1:14:44.480
This is how I feel.

1:14:44.564 --> 1:14:46.441
-This is how I feel.
-(growling)

1:14:46.524 --> 1:14:49.152
This is how I feel
when you come to the platform, okay?

1:14:49.235 --> 1:14:51.279
(hisses, growls)

1:14:51.362 --> 1:14:52.906
Yes, I know.

1:14:52.989 --> 1:14:55.366
You are an angry wild animal,

1:14:55.450 --> 1:14:58.203
but you need to start acting
like a wild animal.

1:14:58.286 --> 1:15:02.040
You need to hunt more.
You need to hunt more.

1:15:04.334 --> 1:15:06.336
(growling)

1:15:09.130 --> 1:15:11.174
SAMANTHA:
A mother ocelot would be brutal,

1:15:11.257 --> 1:15:13.009
like, "You're ready. Goodbye.

1:15:13.092 --> 1:15:15.720
I'm gonna go mate,
and I'm gonna have more."

1:15:15.803 --> 1:15:18.014
It's a totally different relationship.

1:15:18.097 --> 1:15:19.432
Can't compare it.

1:15:19.515 --> 1:15:21.517
♪ ♪

1:15:21.601 --> 1:15:23.311
(yowls)

1:15:26.606 --> 1:15:28.107
Oh.

1:15:29.609 --> 1:15:31.236
Oh, dear.

1:15:32.528 --> 1:15:34.948
God, how did we not hear him over here?

1:15:37.158 --> 1:15:39.160
HARRY: He's just been coming
forwards and backwards,

1:15:39.244 --> 1:15:40.995
forwards and backwards from the platform.

1:15:41.079 --> 1:15:42.747
He went into the rubbish bag.

1:15:42.830 --> 1:15:44.415
He ate a load of plastic.

1:15:44.499 --> 1:15:47.794
I-I went out into the jungle
to look for him the other day,

1:15:47.877 --> 1:15:51.923
and I found a pile of vomit with just,
like, chewed up plastic bag.

1:15:52.006 --> 1:15:55.426
And then he-he takes my towel,

1:15:55.510 --> 1:15:58.012
and he bites a fucking hole in it.

1:16:01.724 --> 1:16:05.353
Every fucking noise,
I'm just like, "Fuck me, is he back?"

1:16:07.647 --> 1:16:09.315
(Harry sighs)

1:16:18.616 --> 1:16:20.660
Go on! (hisses)

1:16:22.328 --> 1:16:24.831
He is so capable of going off by himself,

1:16:24.914 --> 1:16:28.001
but he just won't,
and I don't know what I'm doing wrong.

1:16:31.212 --> 1:16:33.423
But it's now or never.

1:16:33.506 --> 1:16:36.301
He's at the age
where he needs to be leaving me.

1:16:36.384 --> 1:16:39.470
So I need to do everything I can,
whether that be forceful

1:16:39.554 --> 1:16:44.058
or whether that be me getting angry
or scaring him.

1:16:46.060 --> 1:16:47.687
(grunts in frustration)

1:16:58.781 --> 1:17:01.075
(birds calling)

1:17:03.411 --> 1:17:05.621
-(Keanu growling softly)
-(groans)

1:17:07.498 --> 1:17:09.834
(growling)

1:17:09.917 --> 1:17:13.504
(Harry inhales deeply, growls)

1:17:13.588 --> 1:17:17.383
Get off of here! Go. Go.

1:17:17.467 --> 1:17:19.093
Go!

1:17:26.059 --> 1:17:27.977
This is bad.

1:17:29.187 --> 1:17:31.230
Do not come up on here.

1:17:35.109 --> 1:17:37.570
Keanu! Get away!

1:17:39.530 --> 1:17:40.990
Get away!

1:17:41.074 --> 1:17:42.909
Get away now!

1:17:42.992 --> 1:17:44.660
Get away!

1:17:49.707 --> 1:17:52.251
Away! Away!

1:17:55.171 --> 1:17:58.216
Get away! Now!

1:17:58.299 --> 1:17:59.592
Away.

1:17:59.675 --> 1:18:02.470
SAMANTHA:
He has had these moments of rage.

1:18:07.183 --> 1:18:09.018
HARRY:
Basically, you're just telling me that

1:18:09.102 --> 1:18:11.270
I am not doing the right things
and I am wrong.

1:18:11.354 --> 1:18:15.358
So I am fed up, and I take that gun
'cause I want to kill myself.

1:18:15.441 --> 1:18:17.193
But then I think about Jayden,

1:18:17.276 --> 1:18:19.821
I think about my mum
and my dad and my sister,

1:18:19.904 --> 1:18:21.781
and I think about Keanu more than anyone,

1:18:21.864 --> 1:18:23.908
and I think about you
and how that would affect you,

1:18:23.991 --> 1:18:26.786
and I think, how selfish am I being?

1:18:29.622 --> 1:18:33.501
SAMANTHA: I have to, like, almost think
about it as two different people.

1:18:33.584 --> 1:18:35.253
'Cause they really are.

1:18:35.336 --> 1:18:36.587
(Harry grunts in frustration)

1:18:36.671 --> 1:18:38.464
(Harry screams)

1:18:38.548 --> 1:18:39.924
HARRY:
Get off of there!

1:18:40.007 --> 1:18:42.218
Get off of there now!

1:18:42.301 --> 1:18:44.262
(yells)

1:18:44.345 --> 1:18:45.805
Get off.

1:18:50.768 --> 1:18:53.187
I'm worried that he can't live by himself.

1:18:53.271 --> 1:18:56.315
(sighs) And if he can't live
by himself, then f...

1:18:58.693 --> 1:19:00.403
...the past...

1:19:00.486 --> 1:19:04.157
the past 16 months, I've just...

1:19:04.240 --> 1:19:06.159
just failed.

1:19:26.137 --> 1:19:28.514
-SAMANTHA: Please Harry.
-HARRY: I need to do it.

1:19:31.350 --> 1:19:32.894
I need to do it.

1:19:34.479 --> 1:19:36.272
I need to, Sam.

1:19:39.525 --> 1:19:40.902
Leave me alone.

1:19:40.985 --> 1:19:44.947
I need to feel that pain, that adrenaline.
I need to feel it.

1:19:47.325 --> 1:19:50.077
SAMANTHA:
Harry... Har-Harry!

1:19:50.161 --> 1:19:51.871
Please.

1:20:04.175 --> 1:20:06.719
That's what I needed.

1:20:19.649 --> 1:20:23.611
OPERATOR: You have reached
the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline.

1:20:23.694 --> 1:20:25.821
(over phone):
We're here to help.

1:20:28.824 --> 1:20:30.993
RESPONDER:
Hi. This is Lifeline.

1:20:31.077 --> 1:20:33.246
Hi. Um, my name's Samantha.

1:20:33.329 --> 1:20:36.165
I'm calling actually on behalf
of a friend of mine.

1:20:36.249 --> 1:20:37.667
What's going on, Samantha?

1:20:38.751 --> 1:20:41.170
Yeah, so he...
um, he's always been someone

1:20:41.254 --> 1:20:45.049
who self-harms in different ways.

1:20:45.132 --> 1:20:49.679
And I think, like, the first sign
for-for me that things were changing was

1:20:49.762 --> 1:20:53.307
he switched locations
from cutting on the top of his arm,

1:20:53.391 --> 1:20:55.351
and now he's cutting his wrists.

1:20:55.434 --> 1:20:58.396
And the way that he's doing it
is a lot more aggressive.

1:20:58.479 --> 1:21:01.691
